summary: I mentioned this on twitter, but honestly, while a bit overwhelming, I really appreciate the sudden content for Good Omens and...
body:
I mentioned this on twitter, but honestly, while a bit overwhelming, I really appreciate the sudden content for Good Omens and the love people are having for the story

When I was in 7th grade I loved the story so much that I chose to do my end-of-the-year book report on it, and I played out the story with hand made paper puppets to all of my classmates (much to their horror). 

Crowley and War were my favorite characters so I spent extra time on their puppets and my favorite scene of all time was the Plant scene.

tags: I'll follow you into the dark
summary: So, I was listening to I'll Follow You into the dark and I realized it is the perfect song for Aziraphale and Crowley, so I...
artist: Original Song from Death Cab For Cutie. Parody and Singer: Maria Loli
track_name: I'll Follow You Into The Dark (Ineffable Husbands Version)
caption:
So, I was listening to I’ll Follow You into the dark and I realized it is the perfect song for Aziraphale and Crowley, so I decided to make it a little more “them” and this was born. I hope you guys enjoy it. 

Lyrics:

Love of mine
Someday the war might start
But I’ll be close behind
I’ll follow you into the dark
No blinding light
Or tunnels to gates of white
Just our hands clasped so tight
Waiting for forever by your side

If heaven and hell decide
That they both are satisfied
Illuminate the no’s
On their vacancy signs
If there’s no one beside us
We won’t need to fight
And I’ll follow you into the dark

Catholic books
As vicious as roman rule
I got my feelings bruised
By an angel in white
He held my hand
As he told me then
We will never be friends
It’s not only up to us

If heaven and hell decide
That they both are satisfied
Illuminate the no’s
On their vacancy signs
If there’s no one beside us
We won’t need to fight
And I’ll follow you into the dark

You and me, we’ve seen everything to see
From Old Rome to the Ritz
And the sole of our shoes
Are all worn dow
The time to flight is now
But it’s nothing to worry about
Cause we’ll hold each other soon
In the blackest of rooms

If heaven and hell decide
That they both are satisfied
Illuminate the no’s
On their vacancy signs
If there’s no one beside us
We won’t need to fight
And I’ll follow you into the dark
